  "text": "The results of the monthly simulation demonstrate the potential effects of tidal and light cycles on monthly estimates of BMA production. Rates change daily and exhibit high variability at monthly time scales (variance to mean ratio = 26.54). Arbitrarily, or even randomly, choosing sampling days and times will provide little information on true BMA production rates. These results may partially explain the high monthly variability reported for BMA production (see [CITATION_1] .",
